<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1398,2035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1470,1495]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,520,1470,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Dima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtipennis">
<emphasis box="[329,520,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Dima hirtipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an easily recognizable species by its very long semi-erect to erect pubescence all over the body (
<figureCitation box="[354,440,1506,1531]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 59" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,198,1692]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,193,1706]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 59. Habitus images of Dima species. 45 — Dima hirtipennis Platia, 2011, holotype, female, 46 — Dima sp. from Mani; D. hladilorum Schimmel, 1987, 47 — paratype, female, 48 — non-type specimen, male, 49 — non-type specimen, female; D. kozufensis sp. nov., 50 — holotype, male, 51 — paratype, female, 52 — paratype, female, paratype of D. lebenbaueri Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; D. lebenbaueri Schimmel &amp; Platia 2008, 53 — holotype, male, 54 — paratype, female, 55 — non-type specimen, male, 56 — non-type specimen, female; D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993, 57 — holotype, male, 58 — non-type male from Galičica, 59 — non-type female from Galičica Mts. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670797/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 45</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[452,497,1506,1531]" captionStart="FIGURES 131 – 142" captionStartId="48.[151,264,1659,1682]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,205,1632]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[151,1436,193,1638]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURES 131 – 142. Pronotal details of Dima species. 131 — D. fthiotidensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008, paratype, female; 132 — D. scutellaris Platia, 2010, holotype, female; 133 — D. fthiotidensis, male; 134 — D. fthiotidensis, holotype of D. fokidensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; 135 — D. giachinoi Schimmel &amp; Platia 2008, female; 136 — D. hirtipennis Platia, 2011, holotype, female; 137 — D. hladilorum Schimmel, 1987, male; 138 — D. kozufensis sp. nov., paratype, female; 139 — Dima lebenbaueri Schimmel &amp; Platia 2008, holotype, male; 140 — Dima lebenbaueri, non-type specimen, female; 141 — D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993, holotype, female, 142 — D. macedonica, female paratype of D. hladilorum from Galičica Mts. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670821/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">136</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[508,554,1506,1531]" captionStart="FIGURES 163 – 171" captionStartId="51.[151,264,1806,1829]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,202,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[151,1435,193,1785]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURES 163 – 171. Scutellum-shape of Dima species. 163 — D. bruhai sp. nov.; 164 — D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993; 165 — D. raineri Wurst, 1997. Elytral details of Dima species. 166 — D. fthiotidensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; 167 — D. hirtipennis Platia, 2011; 168 — D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993; 169 — D. olympica Meischnigg, 1934; 170 — D. parnonensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; 171 — D. pecoudi Fleutiaux, 1943. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670832/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">167</figureCitation>
). The similar pubescence is known only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Meschnigg, 1934" authorityName="Meschnigg" authorityYear="1934" box="[1037,1375,1506,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Dima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olympica">
<emphasis box="[1037,1057,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1071,1174,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">olympica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meschnigg" box="[1180,1375,1506,1531]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Meschnigg, J. (1934) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Coleopteren vom Balkan. Entomologischer Anzeiger, 14, 65 - 68." type="journal article" year="1934">Meschnigg, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Mt. Olympus, but that species has two 
<typeStatus box="[609,668,1543,1567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">types</typeStatus>
of hairs on the elytra (long erect and short decumbent; 
<figureCitation box="[1323,1424,1542,1567]" captionStart="FIGURES 163 – 171" captionStartId="51.[151,264,1806,1829]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,202,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[151,1435,193,1785]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURES 163 – 171. Scutellum-shape of Dima species. 163 — D. bruhai sp. nov.; 164 — D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993; 165 — D. raineri Wurst, 1997. Elytral details of Dima species. 166 — D. fthiotidensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; 167 — D. hirtipennis Platia, 2011; 168 — D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993; 169 — D. olympica Meischnigg, 1934; 170 — D. parnonensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; 171 — D. pecoudi Fleutiaux, 1943. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670832/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 169</figureCitation>
). Several 
<taxonomicName box="[244,306,1579,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Dima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[244,306,1579,1602]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Dima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from the 
<collectingRegion box="[513,654,1578,1603]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
have also erect pubescence on the pronotum, but shorter (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1431,1578,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 119 – 130" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1659,1682]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,200,1628]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[151,1436,193,1638]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 119 – 130. Pronotal details of Dima species. 119 — D. arndti Platia, 2013, male; 120 — D. assingi Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008, female; 121 — D. bruhai sp. nov., holotype, male; 122 — D. dalmatina Küster, 1844, male; 123 — D. dusaneki sp. nov., holotype, male; 124 — D. elateroides Charpentier, 1825, male; 125 — D. etoliensis Platia, 2012, holotype, female; 126 — D. evritaniensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008, paratype, female; 127 — D. evritaniensis, male; 128 — D. fialai sp. nov., holotype, male; 129 — D. florinensis Platia, 2012, female; 130 — D. fthiotidensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008, male. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670817/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 120</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,195,1614,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 143 – 154" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1663,1686]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,202,1631]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1436,193,1642]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 143 – 154. Pronotal details of Dima species. 143 — D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993, male; 144 — D. marvani Mertlik &amp; Dusanek, 2006, holotype, male; 145 — D. moraveci Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008, holotype, female; 146 — D. neumanni Platia, 2013, female; 147 — D. olympica Meschnigg, 1934, male; 148 — D. orientalis sp. nov., holotype, male; 149 — D. parnonensis Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008, female; 150 — D. pecoudi Fleutiaux, 1944, male; 151 — D. pelikani sp. nov., holotype, male; 152 — D. pelionensis sp. nov., paratype, female, 153 — D. pelionensis sp. nov., paratype, female paratype of D. fokidensis; 154 — D. raineri Wurst, 1997, female. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670825" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670825/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">146</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[207,253,1614,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 155 – 162" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1181,1204]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,198,1150]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[150,1436,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 155 – 162. Pronotal details of Dima species. 155 — D. raineri Wurst, 1997, holotype, male; 156 — D. schimmeli Platia &amp; Gudenzi, 2009, female; 157 — D. schnitteri Platia, 2013, female; 158 — D. vailatii Schimmel &amp; Platia 2008, holotype, male; 159 — D. vailatii, male; 160 — D. riesei Platia, 2010, holotype, male; 161 — D. vonickai sp. nov., holotype, male; 162 — D. zbuzeki sp. nov., holotype, male. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670830/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">157</figureCitation>
