<figureCitation box="[391,521,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 59" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,198,1692]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,193,1706]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 59. Habitus images of Dima species. 45 — Dima hirtipennis Platia, 2011, holotype, female, 46 — Dima sp. from Mani; D. hladilorum Schimmel, 1987, 47 — paratype, female, 48 — non-type specimen, male, 49 — non-type specimen, female; D. kozufensis sp. nov., 50 — holotype, male, 51 — paratype, female, 52 — paratype, female, paratype of D. lebenbaueri Schimmel &amp; Platia, 2008; D. lebenbaueri Schimmel &amp; Platia 2008, 53 — holotype, male, 54 — paratype, female, 55 — non-type specimen, male, 56 — non-type specimen, female; D. macedonica Schimmel, 1993, 57 — holotype, male, 58 — non-type male from Galičica, 59 — non-type female from Galičica Mts. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4670797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4670797/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<collectorName box="[391,441,1938,1963]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs</collectorName>
45–46
</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having a darker body (light brown in 
<taxonomicName box="[1265,1419,1939,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Dima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtipennis">
<emphasis box="[1265,1419,1939,1963]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D. hirtipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), different shape of pronotum, with slightly longer pubescence on the pronotal sides, and straight frontal margin of scutellum (distinctly emarginate in 
<taxonomicName box="[572,733,2011,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Dima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtipennis">
<emphasis box="[572,733,2011,2035]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D. hirtipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<collectorName box="[763,825,2010,2035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Since</collectorName>
we have only two specimens from different sexes available for the study, we cannot assess what is the the sexual dimorphism and what is the interspecific difference. 
<collectorName box="[151,264,188,213]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Therefore</collectorName>
, it seems the best approach is to postpone any taxonomic decision until more material from the southern 
<collectingRegion box="[151,292,223,248]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
is available.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
